    {
      "title": "Minimum value = c - b²/(4a) — no need to find x first",
      "content": "For $f(x) = x^2 - 12x + 30$, use $a = 1$, $b = -12$, $c = 30$. The minimum value is $c - \\frac{b^2}{4a} = 30 - \\frac{(-12)^2}{4(1)} = 30 - \\frac{144}{4} = 30 - 36 = -6$."
    },
    {
      "title": "Result",
      "content": "The minimum value of $f$ is $-6$. That confirms <strong>B</strong> is correct."
    }
  ]
}
